  "description": [
    "THE SILVER STATE VOL LII WINNEMUCCA NEVADA MONDAY MAY 2 1898 NO 13 Washington May 2The United States Asiatic squadron has destroyed the Spanish fleet in the harbor of Manila The United States Asiatic squadron under command of Commodore Dewey yes j terday engaged and completely defeated the Spanish Asiatic squadron Admiral Montijo commanding in the harbor of Manila The Spanish fleet lost three of its best ships The cruiser Reina Cristinafhe Spanish Admirals flagshipand the cruiser Castilla were burned The cruiser Don Juan de Austria was blown up Two brisk engagements were fought In the first the Spanish ships were dam aged but not seriously The American ships maneuvered for position and the Spanish thought they were retreating Great excitement followed Gaining the desired position the American fleet reopened fire The first shell from the Baltimore struck the Reina Cristina setting that cruiser I on fire The attempt to quench the flames failing Admiral Montijo transferred the flag to the cruiser Isla de Cuba Just as the admiral left the ship another shell struck I the deck killing the captain j A well directed shot reached the steel cruiser Don Juan de Austria and a ter rific exrlosion followed"
  ],
